data.title: Normal
data.text: Not so good, but its okay the service is fast but the pizza with peperoni is not so taste. Any way enjoy your experience

data.title: Reasonable pies
data.text: While not the best pie in town, Pizza Mia does have a nice sauce - slightly sweet but with distinctive oregano flavor - which is layered on a crisply baked dough. The cheese is straight mozzarella without much fanfare - some are nutty but this is whole milk without any additional aspects. I always get the pepperoni which is thin and crisp, and usually plentiful. I have tried a few other toppings but this is the standout. Quick delivery and the order taker has always been easy to understand and also understands me - not always the case with other places in new brunswick.
